    "description": "Seattle's iconic public market overlooking Elliott Bay, home to over 200 local artisans, farmers, and small businesses. Famous for the fish-throwing fishmongers, the original Starbucks, the Gum Wall, and award-winning clam chowder. One of the oldest continuously operated public farmers' markets in the US.",
    "considerations": [
      "Arrive early (before 10am) to beat the crowds and get the best produce",
      "The market is busiest on weekends \u2014 weekday mornings are much calmer",
      "Watch for the fish toss at Pike Place Fish Market",
      "The Gum Wall is a short walk down Post Alley \u2014 worth a quick stop",
      "Many vendors are cash-preferred"
    ]
