    "description": "Seattle's most iconic landmark, standing 605 feet tall with two observation levels offering 360-degree views of the city skyline, Mount Rainier, Elliott Bay, and the Olympic and Cascade mountain ranges. Features a unique rotating glass floor called The Loupe. The on-site restaurant, Atmos, rotates with panoramic views.",
    "considerations": [
      "Book tickets online in advance \u2014 walk-up lines can be very long in August",
      "Sunset visits (around 8:30pm in August) offer spectacular lighting",
      "Dining at the restaurant includes complimentary observation deck access",
      "The glass floor on the observation deck can be unsettling for those with a fear of heights"
    ]
  },
