    "description": "The 28th annual Capitol Hill Block Party runs August 7\u20139, 2026, in Seattle's vibrant Pike/Pine corridor. This three-day music and arts festival features 100+ performances across indoor and outdoor stages including headliners MUNA, Wet Leg, and Disco Lines, plus Magdalena Bay, Parcels, Tinashe DJ Set, and many more. More than half the lineup is Seattle-based artists.",
    "considerations": [
      "Event is 21+ \u2014 valid government-issued ID required for entry",
      "August 4 is before the festival (Aug 7\u20139) \u2014 plan accordingly if visiting for multiple days",
      "Three-day passes and single-day passes available; book in advance",
      "Stages span multiple indoor venues including Neumos and Barboza",
      "Expect large crowds and limited parking \u2014 use public transit or rideshare",
      "Surge pricing on rideshares during peak hours"
