    "description": "Seattle's original narrated harbor cruise, operating since 1949. This one-hour tour of Elliott Bay offers panoramic views of the Seattle skyline, Space Needle, Olympic Mountains, Mount Rainier, and one of the West Coast's busiest shipping ports. A full-service bar with cocktails, local wine, beer, and snacks is available on board.",
    "considerations": [
      "Book tickets online in advance to save money and guarantee a spot",
      "Sit on the port side (left facing forward) for the best skyline and Space Needle views",
      "The upper deck offers better photos but no window glare protection",
      "Arrive at least 20\u201330 minutes before departure for boarding",
      "Harbor porpoises are commonly spotted May\u2013August",
      "A CityPASS bundle can save significantly if combining with other attractions"
    ]
  },
