    "description": "A guided walking tour through the historic underground passageways beneath Pioneer Square, dating back to the 1890s. After the Great Seattle Fire of 1889, the city was rebuilt one story higher, leaving the original street level intact underground. The tour is humorous and historically rich, covering Seattle's colorful early history.",
    "considerations": [
      "Book tickets in advance \u2014 tours fill up quickly in summer",
      "The tour involves walking on uneven surfaces; wear comfortable, closed-toe shoes",
      "Not recommended for those with claustrophobia or mobility issues",
      "Tours depart from Doc Maynard's Public House in Pioneer Square",
      "The humor is adult-oriented \u2014 may not be suitable for young children"
    ]
